    "plan_content": "Here's my plan summary:\n\n## Plan: `uv cache stats` Subcommand\n\nAfter thoroughly exploring the codebase, I've confirmed all the patterns needed. Here are the **4 files to change + 1 new file**:\n\n### What I found\n\n- `CacheCommand` enum lives at **line 878–905** of `crates/uv-cli/src/lib.rs`; `SizeArgs` is at lines 947–952\n- `CacheCommand::Size` dispatch is at **line 1179–1181** of `crates/uv/src/lib.rs`\n- `cache_size.rs` uses `diskus::DiskUsage::new(vec![path]).count_ignoring_errors()` — same approach for per-bucket\n- `human_readable_bytes` is re-exported from `uv_console` via `crate::commands::human_readable_bytes`\n- `CacheBucket::iter()` yields **10 buckets** (intentionally excludes `Python`)\n- `Cache::bucket(bucket)` returns `self.root.join(bucket.to_str())`\n- `CacheBucket`'s `Display` uses `to_str()` → e.g. `\"wheels-v6\"`, `\"sdists-v9\"`, etc.\n\n### Key design decisions\n1. **No preview gate** — `cache_stats` is implemented directly unlike `cache_size` which has a `PreviewFeature::CacheSize` guard\n2. **Missing-bucket safety** — each bucket path is checked with `.exists()` before calling `DiskUsage`, so an empty cache prints `0` rather than crashing\n3. **`StatsArgs`** mirrors `SizeArgs` exactly (same `--human`/`-H`/`--human-readable` flag)\n4. The dispatch call signature is `commands::cache_stats(&cache, args.human, printer)` — no `globals.preview` parameter",
